VARIABLES:
-piece of memory used to  store a data value.
-in java,it is a memeber of class.

TYPES:
Local variable
Instance variable
Class/Static variable

LOCAL VARIABLE:
  declared within the method of a class.
INSTANCE VARIABLE:
 declared outside a method/constructor/any block.
CLASS /STATIC VARIABLE:
 declared within class
 keyword "STATIC" is specified with claas variable
***
 INSTANCE VARIABLE   /  CLS VARIABLES:
 Class variables are declared with keyword static and Instance variables are declared without static keyword.
 Class variables are common to all instances of a class.
 These variables are shared between the objects of a class


 class A
 {
 static int a=10; // CLASS VARAIBLE
 int z; // INSTANCE VARIABLE
 public static void main(String args[])
 {
 A a=new A();
 a.show(2);
 }
 void show(int a)
 {
 int x; // LOCAL VARAIBLE
 x=a+5;
 System.out.println(x);
 }
 }

 DATA TYPES:
   -integer
   -float
   -character
   -boolean

  integer:
    byte(1 byte)
    short(2 byte)
    int(4 byte)
    long(8 byte)
  float:
    float(4 byte)
    double(8 byte)
  character:
    char(1 byte)
  boolean:
   bool(maximum 1 byte i.e...takes less thn tht)
    
